        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 26</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Owing to the disturbance of our P. Office at Xmas, I received only tonight your note of the 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.— It is clear that either I or the Printers have omitted accidentally “from a mare”.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> You are the most accurate of Translators that ever lived.—</p>
<p>I return with much sincerity your good wishes, &amp; may your life long be spared | Yours very truly | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes"> 
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11286.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 23 December 1877</ref>.</note>
